# Kubernetes CronJob Job History

For **one-shot / agent-style CronJobs** (e.g. x-post-agent, sentiment, discovery, scraping):

- **successfulJobsHistoryLimit: 1** — Keep only the most recent successful run. We don't need a long tail of completed jobs.
- **failedJobsHistoryLimit: 2** — Keep a couple of failed runs for debugging; then they age out.

Always set these explicitly so we don't accumulate many completed Job objects. Defaults in Kubernetes can retain more than we want.
